  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "To delete Gmail from one device while keeping it on other devices, follow these steps:\n\n1. On the device you want to remove Gmail:\n\n\u2022 Go to Settings\n\u2022 Select \"Accounts\" or \"Mail & Accounts\"\n\u2022 Tap on your Google/Gmail account\n\u2022 Select \"Remove Account\" or \"Delete Account\"\n\n2. On other devices, your Gmail will remain intact\n\nAlternative methods:\n\nMobile (Gmail App):\n\u2022 Open Gmail app\n\u2022 Go to Settings\n\u2022 Select the account\n\u2022 Choose \"Remove account\"\n\niOS Devices:\n\u2022 Settings \u2192 Mail \u2192 Accounts\n\u2022 Select Gmail\n\u2022 Tap \"Delete Account\"\n\nAndroid Devices:\n\u2022 Settings \u2192 Accounts\n\u2022 Select Gmail account\n\u2022 Tap \"Remove Account\"\n\nImportant notes:\n\u2022 This only removes the account from that specific device\n\u2022 Your emails remain synced on other devices\n\u2022 You can always re-add the account later\n\u2022 Your cloud data and emails are not deleted\n\nPro Tip: Before removing, ensure you've backed up any important emails or attachments you might need.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
